cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is about deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of neural networks and policy gradient methods suggests that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The focus on learning complex policies and the use of physics simulators suggest that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of image-based inputs and the potential for computer vision applications suggest that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of control theory and the focus on continuous action spaces suggest that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
